messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 2/19/2003 3:24:05 PM Central Standard Time,
Unschooling-dotcom@yahoogroups.com writes:


> This person will be 41 this year, and her
> FSH level was 15.8. I know next to nothing about this. Anyone who has info
> on how to become pregnant with high FSH levels, write me please?

The best site I can recommend is ONNA.org. There's a lot of stuff out there
and a lot of books recommended on the site.

My sister was 41 (as were her eggs) when we attempted to have me be a
surrogate using her and her husband's embryo and my uterus. It was
unsuccessful. There are other options. ONNA is where I'd start.

Elizabeth
